description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job title: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead Assistant Technical Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;London (see advert below) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;£21,000 - £23,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 hours per week, Monday to Sunday &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;InHealth is one of the UK’s leading healthcare providers and has a strong track record delivering modern and efficient healthcare services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We now have an opening for a &lt;strong&gt;Lead Assistant Technical Officer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our PhysMed team in London, covering our diagnostic centres in &lt;strong&gt;Ealing, Enfield, Golders Green and Stratford&lt;/strong&gt;. This role is full time working 37.5 hours per week on a rota shift pattern basis from &lt;strong&gt;Monday to Sunday. &lt;/strong&gt;There may be occasional travel to other sites - all travel expenses will be covered by InHealth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the overall purpose of the role?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To lead and support the Physiological Measurement service in the delivery of Resting ECG, Ambulatory ECG and BP monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the key responsibilities?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare patients for and perform resting ECGs in accordance with AHA specifications and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fit and remove ambulatory ECG and BP monitors, giving the patient clear instructions and advice relating to the period of monitoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, motivate and manage the performance of clinical staff through the sharing of knowledge and clinical expertise, managing absence and productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor adherence and compliance to all operational procedures and policies as outlined by the Company, escalating any concerns to the Regional Operations Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate active involvement in the recruitment, appointment and induction of new staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct appraisals gaining feedback from other relevant members of staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the rota for the ATO team to ensure effective and cost-efficient service delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you need in order to apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of working as an ATO or Cardiographer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, written, verbal and listening&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership qualities and ability to manage a busy workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to remain calm and focused in challenging situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstratable teaching and coaching skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s on offer for you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous flexible benefits package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private medical insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days holiday + bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In addition, we are committed to offering on-going investment and support in professional development, creating a natural career path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
